    commonMistakes: ['Assuming RAG eliminates all hallucinations it reduces them significantly but does not guarantee perfect accuracy.', 'Poor chunking strategy chunks that are too small lack context while chunks that are too large include irrelevant information that confuses the LLM.', 'Forgetting that retrieval quality is the bottleneck a bad retriever means bad RAG regardless of the LLM quality.'],
    sharkTankExample: 'A legal-tech startup pitches an AI contract analyst using RAG to search through thousands of past contracts. The sharks ask about accuracy. The founder demonstrates how the system retrieves specific clauses from the company own document repository, grounding every answer in a retrievable source.',
