    definition: 'Fine-tuning is a transfer learning technique where a pre-trained model is further trained on a smaller, task-specific dataset to adapt its capabilities for a particular use case. Rather than training a model from scratch which requires enormous computational resources and data, fine-tuning starts with a model that already understands language patterns and gently adjusts its weights to specialize. Full fine-tuning updates all model parameters, while parameter-efficient methods like LoRA modify only a small subset, drastically reducing cost.',
