    commonMistakes: ['Assuming clusters found by unsupervised learning are real different algorithms produce different clusters.', 'Using Euclidean distance for high-dimensional data it becomes meaningless curse of dimensionality.', 'Not preprocessing data features with different scales dominate distance calculations always normalize.'],
    sharkTankExample: 'A startup pitches an AI that segments retail customers into behavioral groups using unsupervised learning. The algorithm discovered a previously unknown segment: weekend bargain hunters who buy premium coffee.',
