    interviewQuestions: ['How does a convolution operation work on an image?', 'What is the role of pooling layers in CNNs?', 'Explain how parameter sharing makes CNNs efficient for image processing.', 'What is the difference between a CNN and a fully connected network for images?', 'How do modern architectures like ResNet and EfficientNet improve upon basic CNNs?'],
    commonMistakes: ['Using fully connected layers instead of convolutions for image data leads to far too many parameters and overfitting.', 'Applying pooling too aggressively losing spatial information needed for precise localization.', 'Using too few filters in early layers missing basic features that later layers depend on.'],
